        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 4:37PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 437 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Coldwater, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Angola, Fremont, Ray, Kinderhook, California, Clear Lake, Lake James,
Lake Of The Woods, Crooked Lake, and Coldwater Lake.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 69 in Indiana between mile markers 350 and 357.
Interstate 69 in Michigan between mile markers 1 and 10.
Interstate 80 in Indiana between mile markers 140 and 153.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
